--situation: Refactoring or writing any .go file under engram/internal or engram/cmd, before running targ check-full
--behavior: The strict targ check-full lint config rejects patterns that pass a naive first draft: top-level var (gochecknoglobals; only sentinel errors allowed), cyclomatic complexity >10 (cyclop), declarations placed before their consumers (reorder-decls-check), functions returning literal nil instead of []T{
--impact: Missing these on the first pass burns 30+ tool-use iteration
